  "texts": [
    "The following proposition characterizes the thresholds for the amount of specic capital and summarizes the non-monotonic response of factor prices to the accumulation of this specic capital analytically.",
    "Proposition 13 (Specic capital and factor returns).",
    "Suppose that the current amount of the specic capital is given by k(I t).",
    "There are threshold values k 1 and k 2 > k 1 such that (i) if k(I t) < k 1 then the wage decreases and the rental rate of the traditional capital increases with k(I t), (ii) if k 1 ≤ k(I t) < k 2 then both the wage and the rental rate of traditional capital increase with k(I t), and (iii) if k(I t) ≥ k 2 then specic capital k(I t) is only accumulated alongside traditional capital, and the wage increases with capital accumulation.",
    "See appendix."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}